name: yakyak
description: Desktop chat client for Google Hangouts

releases.body:
- internationalization #526 
- more efficient startup and redraws #549 
- open videos and better handle google plus contents in general #535 
- line breaks from android app are now rendered correctly #558 
- fix presence handling and reporting
- fix windows taskbar app name from electron to yakyak #580
- set as online with every connection cycle #167 
- improves on emoji support in linux and windows 8.1/10 #562 
- fix tray icon as it wasn't being updated with read/unread information #566

We suggest to perform a logout/login cycle for these fixes to work correctly (#535)

- notifications improvements [#467]
- small fixes creating/removing conversations [#476]
- show participant reading status in conversations [#483]
- ui improvements
- performance improvements, lower CPU usage in idle and avoid GPU usage
- Fix failed to append child error [#518]
- only plays custom audio if notifications are on [#539]
- fixes exception with leaving conversation [#524]

## 1.4.0 full list of new features/fix/experimental
- [MAJOR FIX] Google changed protocol. This version works with the new version

### New Features:
- [FEATURE] Embedded photos in chat messages (#407)
- [FEATURE] Image preview when pasting or adding images via selector (#398)
- [FEATURE] 'Help -> About' window (#423)
- [FEATURE] Add startup screen and fix window position on startup (#418)
- [FEATURE] Switching between hide window and clear input when pressing 'escape' key (#409)
- [FEATURE] Feature Request: Notification Privacy (#386 and #399)
- [FEATURE] Add "show popup notifications" option to tray (#393)
- [FEATURE] Debugging: All errors from main window are shown in command line (#426)
- [FEATURE] clears input when changing conversations, remembers when returns to it #76 #458
- [FEATURE] new packaging method
- [FEATURE] clears input when changing conversations, remembers when returns to it #76 #458
- [FEATURE] new packaging method

### Bug fixes
- [FIX] bad avatar and wrong initials #74
- [FIX] Copy/Paste/Cut working on MacOSX
- [FIX] Native about window problem solved, now calls on new "About" (MacOSX)
  - Help menu item is removed from MacOSX
- [FIX] Send same image to two contacts in a row #450 
- [FIX] About window is now created on demand instead of being pre-loaded at the beginning.
- [FIX] Fix on not fitting images in conversations list (#430)
- [Fix] menu icon in dark scheme (#433 and #437)
- [Fix] fallback to initials when thumbnail image not available #428
- [FIX] fix deploy.sh and add --no-zip option (#424)
- [FIX] Fix 'event.keyIdentifier' depreciation in favour of 'event.key' (#419)
- [FIX] fixes three bugs with emojis (#412 and #413)
- [FIX] menus had a typo 'getAccelarator' should be 'getAccelerator' (#403)
- [FIX] Make hide the window (close to tray) work on all platforms if "Close (#397)
- [FIX] Copy/Paste/Cut working on MacOSX
- [FIX] Native about window problem solved, now calls on new "About" (MacOSX)
  - Help menu item is removed from MacOSX
- [FIX] Send same image to two contacts in a row #450 
- [FIX] About window is now created on demand instead of being pre-loaded at the beginning.
- [FIX] bad avatar and wrong initials #74

### Experimental (now fully working)
- [Experimental] Shows who has seen each message group (#429)

v1.3.2
- Fix login to work after breaking Google API change
- Fix leaving conversation
- Better handle emojis expansion while writing
- Monocrome tray icon
- I am sure there is something else but i don't remember :)

- Add coloscheme menu for Windows and Linux
- Better compression for osx package
- Show / hide conversation timestamp / last message
- Fix issues on window resize
- Add hambuger menu and hide menu bar (on Windows/Linux)
- Fix odd behavours on Windows
- Add ability to change font size
- Add shortcode emoji support
- Hide window on ESC key
- Linux: flash task bar on notification
- [..]

- New UI with 4 color schemes (themes)
- Support for user presence
- OSX integration with the window titlebar
- Show hangout events in conversations
- Other fixes and improvements..

- Fix missing user icons
- Fix application flashing when changing conversation
- Fix missing directory error on first launch

1.2.2
- fix login bug

1.2.1
- fix empty messages
- electron version 1.2.1 (yea, same version as ours)

Cows are go!

releases.name: v1.1.3
releases.body:
- emoticons support (special thanks to @mhogerheijde)
- more robust login procedure
- better tray/menubar icon handling
- minimize-to-tray feature
- application can start minimized to tray
- tray icon finally reflects unread status (for unmuted conversations)
- minor fixes

Notes: We develop on MacOS and we can't test everything on all OS on every release. Thank you everyone for your help reporting issues.

releases.body:
- Login fixed

releases.name: v1.1.1
releases.body:
- electron 0.34.1
- hangupjs 1.2
- minor improvements
- check latest version on startup

releases.name: v1.1.0
releases.body:
Notable changes
- favorite (starred) conversations
- electron 0.30.2
- keyboard conv nav skip hidden pure hangouts
- conversation settings improvements

Graduating this to 1.0.0. Doesn't mean everything is perfect, just that it's stable enough.

Notable changes:
- Proxy detection
- Audible notifications
- Keyboard to move between convs
- Better online/offline detection
- Message times on hover

releases.name: beta3
releases.body:
Various fixes given feedback on the second beta. Notably:
- Logout really do clean cookies on windows
- Missing OSX shortcuts (fullscreen, hide)
- Tooltips on buttons
- Attach image button for non-drag-droppers
- Bug fix writes to app dir (thanks @maxkueng)
- Binaries for win-x64 and linux-x64 (we're in the future after all)
